snippet.title: SNES Iron Commando
snippet.description: Now this game is very interesting. Developed by Arcade Zone of "Legend" (in?)fame, "Iron Commando" is a side scrolling beat'em'up influenced in my opinion by such Capcom classics of the genre like "Punisher" (which was indeed converted to Megadrive but sadly not SNES). This Japanese version (full title "Iron Commando - Kotetsu no Senshi") is the only released version of the game however the fully working, level select enabled English PAL ROM prototype exists and has been dumped quite some time ago, leaving up the mystery: Why didn't any publishers picked it up in 1994? We will never know, but please enjoy this game that like it's predecessor "Legend" boasts some very impressive graphics.
